<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The code computes copy_size = response->data_iovcnt * sizeof(MHD_iovec_) and then does memcpy(connection->rp.resp_iov.iov, response->data_iov, copy_size) without validating response->data_iovcnt or guarding against integer overflow or verifying that response->data_iov actually refers to an object at least that large. If response->data_iovcnt is corrupted or maliciously large (or multiplication overflows on size_t), memcpy can read beyond the bounds of response->data_iov (and could also write beyond the allocated destination if allocation/overflow interactions occur). Example: a corrupted response->data_iovcnt causes copy_size to exceed the actual bytes in response->data_iov, so memcpy accesses past the source buffer — violating Rule 21.17.
</scenario>

